Class MovingObject

java.lang.Object

public class MovingObject
extends java.lang.Object

Represents the player and enemies in the game. Provides physics based movement (see update(float) and a draw method.

Method Detail

update

public void update(float deltaTime)
Updates position of object based on gravity and jumpforce.checkGravity() is called first. After which: 
 Create PointF with gravity force as its y value;
 Create gravityStep by multiplying by deltaTime; 
 
 Add gravityStep to velocity;
 
 Create new PointF with jump force as its y value;
 
 if(player is jumping and is on ground) {
                add jumping force to velocity;
 } else {
                if(gravity is not reversed) {
                        if(player is not jumping and velocity.y > jumpcutoff) {
                                set velocity y value to equal jumpCutOff;
                        } 
                } else {
                        if(player is not jumping and velocity.y < jumpCutOff) {
                                set velocity y value to equal jumpCutOff;
                        }
                }
 }
 
 Truncate force to minimum/maximum;
 
 Multiple velocity by delta time and add to players desired position;
A desired position is used because if the player is intersecting with a wall the players desired position is fixed by Map.checkObjectCollisionWithFloor(MovingObject) before setting the payers position to equal desired position.

checkGravity

public void checkGravity()
Invoked by update(float) before force is applied. Checks if gravity is reversed in Settings.isGravityReversed(): 
 if(gravity is not reversed) {
        gravity force = -Max_gravity constant;
        jump = minus MAX_JUMP constant;
                        jumpCutOff = minus MAX_JUMP_CUT_OFF constant;
 } else {
        gravity = MAX_GRAVITY constant;
                        jump =  minus MAX_JUMP;
                        jumpCutOff = minus MAX_JUMP_CUT_OFF;
 }
